# Agent Harness Map

This project ships agent knowledge for multiple harnesses. Prefer Cursor paths first.

| Source harness | Path | Cursor equivalent |
|----------------|------|-------------------|
| Copilot instructions | `.github/copilot-instructions.md` | `.cursor/rules/kmp-*.mdc` |
| Copilot memories | `.github/copilot-memories.md` | `AGENTS.md` |
| Copilot skills | `.github/skills/<name>/` | `.cursor/skills/<name>/` (symlink) |
| Copilot prompts | `.github/prompts/*.prompt.md` | `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` |
| Claude Code skills | `.claude/skills/` | Prefer `.github/skills/` copies |
| Constitution | `.specify/memory/constitution.md` | `kmp-core.mdc` summary |

## Cursor-only workflow skills

| Copilot prompt | Cursor skill |
|----------------|--------------|
| `sync-changelog.prompt.md` | `sync-changelog` |
| `doublcheckdocs.prompt.md` | `double-check-docs` |

When a skill references a prompt file, follow that file's workflow exactly.

## Docker dev workflow (Cursor agents)

Local development uses **Docker Compose with bind-mounted source**. Agents should:

1. Edit code in the workspace (host paths under `./app`)
2. Run migrations, tests, and verification **via repo-root scripts or `docker compose exec app`**
3. Reset databases with **`./dev-reset-db.sh`** or **`./dev-reset-db.sh --seed`** — not bare-host PHP against `db`

See `AGENTS.md` § Dev environment and `docs/docker-development.md`.
